1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:40,640
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP02]

3
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:42,519
Here, Miss Ruan.

4
00:01:43,359 --> 00:01:43,879
Come on in.
Thanks.

5
00:02:10,879 --> 00:02:11,520
Mr. Liu.
I got it.

6
00:02:12,719 --> 00:02:13,759
No problem. It's nothing.

7
00:02:23,080 --> 00:02:23,800
Let me. Thanks.

8
00:02:43,039 --> 00:02:43,879
You two know each other?

9
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:50,800
No. No, we don't.

10
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:01,120
No.

11
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:05,879
Let me introduce you then.

12
00:03:06,439 --> 00:03:06,879
This is
our firm's legal counsel,

13
00:03:07,879 --> 00:03:08,319
Xu Huaisong.

14
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:18,479
Hello.

15
00:03:23,039 --> 00:03:23,479
And this

16
00:03:23,479 --> 00:03:24,759
is our client for this case.

17
00:03:25,159 --> 00:03:25,759
Ruan Yu.

18
00:03:26,879 --> 00:03:27,599
Miss Ruan.

19
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:30,039
A novelist.

20
00:03:30,639 --> 00:03:31,879
Specializes in romance.

21
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:38,599
Mr. Xu, how'd you know that?

22
00:03:39,240 --> 00:03:40,599
I looked over your file.

23
00:03:49,680 --> 00:03:52,560
And how much do you know?

24
00:03:55,159 --> 00:03:58,000
About the case? Or about the person?

25
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,360
Or maybe your novel?

26
00:04:06,439 --> 00:04:08,159
Mr. Xu just means

27
00:04:08,439 --> 00:04:09,039
we'd like to

28
00:04:09,039 --> 00:04:10,199
get some basic info

29
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:11,719
on our clients before the discussion.

30
00:04:11,719 --> 00:04:12,240
It's part

31
00:04:12,240 --> 00:04:13,719
of being

32
00:04:14,159 --> 00:04:14,759
a good lawyer,
right?

33
00:04:16,439 --> 00:04:17,519
Got the basics covered.

34
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:19,439
Haven't read the novel yet, right?

35
00:04:20,839 --> 00:04:21,560
Oh right, Miss Ruan,

36
00:04:21,839 --> 00:04:22,959
you brought the novel, yeah?

37
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:30,720
I... Yeah.

38
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:31,839
Good.

39
00:04:31,839 --> 00:04:32,959
Just hand it to Mr. Xu

40
00:04:32,959 --> 00:04:33,480
later.

41
00:04:33,959 --> 00:04:34,560
Have a seat.

42
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:36,040
Here.

43
00:04:42,879 --> 00:04:44,040
[This novel is basically]

44
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,720
[a full-on fantasy]

45
00:04:47,439 --> 00:04:49,800
[about Xu Huaisong,]

46
00:04:49,800 --> 00:04:51,079
[from his body to his soul.]

47
00:04:52,439 --> 00:04:54,079
[And now I have to]

48
00:04:54,759 --> 00:04:56,399
[give it to him,]

49
00:04:57,399 --> 00:04:59,199
[and then dive]

50
00:04:59,879 --> 00:05:00,959
[into a legal discussion]

51
00:05:01,519 --> 00:05:03,399
[about the fantasy]

52
00:05:03,839 --> 00:05:05,439
[with him?]

53
00:05:08,439 --> 00:05:09,319
Gentlemen,
as they say,

54
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:11,279
let mercy guide your hand.

55
00:05:11,279 --> 00:05:12,160
Patience brings peace.
A step back gives room to breathe.

56
00:05:13,519 --> 00:05:15,399
Saving a life is the greatest virtue.

57
00:05:19,279 --> 00:05:20,560
Miss Ruan, what do you mean?

58
00:05:21,439 --> 00:05:22,879
I... I mean,

59
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:24,920
I suddenly don't wanna sue anymore.

60
00:05:26,319 --> 00:05:27,120
Don't wanna sue?

61
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,160
Are you... sure about that?

62
00:05:40,439 --> 00:05:41,079
Just a sec.
I gotta take this.

63
00:05:41,879 --> 00:05:42,600
Sorry.

64
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:49,560
Hello?

65
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:51,800
What kind of delivery

66
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:52,839
needs my signature in person?

67
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,279
Okay. Coming.

68
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:00,839
She suddenly doesn't wanna sue?

69
00:06:04,199 --> 00:06:05,160
Did I do something wrong?

70
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:18,480
Mr. Liu's pretty busy, huh?

71
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,079
Last time I saw him,

72
00:06:20,959 --> 00:06:22,560
he also had to step out

73
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:23,439
for a call.

74
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:28,360
Last time?

75
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:36,759
Please.

76
00:07:58,079 --> 00:08:00,759
[He barely changed.]

77
00:08:02,319 --> 00:08:05,800
[Time's been way too kind to him.]

78
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:14,680
Miss Ruan,
you got a problem with me?

79
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:19,240
No, no.

80
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:20,720
Wouldn't dare.

81
00:08:21,680 --> 00:08:22,600
Just

82
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,439
feeling sorry for myself.

83
00:09:18,039 --> 00:09:18,919
What's up, Mr. Xu?

84
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:24,519
Sorry.
Had to go downstairs

85
00:09:25,279 --> 00:09:26,360
to sign for a package.

86
00:09:29,039 --> 00:09:29,840
So, Miss Ruan,

87
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,080
have you made up your mind?

88
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,799
Mr. Liu, I've thought it through.

89
00:09:34,480 --> 00:09:34,840
Alright.

90
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,240
I respect your decision.

91
00:09:37,120 --> 00:09:38,480
I've had plenty of clients

92
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:40,200
who hesitate at the last minute.

93
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,279
But after thinking it over,

94
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:44,240
they usually go through with the lawsuit.

95
00:09:44,799 --> 00:09:46,000
It's fine. Take your time.

96
00:09:47,759 --> 00:09:48,720
Mr. Liu, you're talking

97
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,039
about your divorce clients, right?

98
00:09:51,480 --> 00:09:53,200
Those two don't get along?

99
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,360
Thanks, Mr. Liu.

100
00:09:59,639 --> 00:10:00,840
I'll think about it some more.

101
00:10:01,159 --> 00:10:03,000
Sure. Let me walk you out.

102
00:10:04,200 --> 00:10:04,639
Don't bother.

103
00:10:05,399 --> 00:10:06,080
Go ahead with your work.

104
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,840
Running back and forth now

105
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:08,600
will make you late for lunch.

106
00:10:08,879 --> 00:10:09,720
I'm not busy.

107
00:10:10,159 --> 00:10:12,000
I was just about to invite you to lunch.

108
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:14,360
Then let me treat you.

109
00:10:14,639 --> 00:10:15,279
It's too much trouble for you.
Alright.

110
00:10:17,159 --> 00:10:17,720
Western food?

111
00:10:19,080 --> 00:10:19,799
There is a Western restaurant
near where she lived.

112
00:10:21,039 --> 00:10:21,360
Sure.

113
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:33,200
So you two already made plans for lunch?

114
00:10:37,039 --> 00:10:37,639
I forgot about that.

115
00:10:39,360 --> 00:10:40,279
How about next time?

116
00:10:42,080 --> 00:10:44,440
But he's already gone downstairs.

117
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:49,399
It's okay. I'll go tell him.

118
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:50,279
Let's go.

119
00:11:05,679 --> 00:11:06,480
Wait for me upstairs.

120
00:11:06,879 --> 00:11:08,559
I'll drop Ruan Yu off

121
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,120
and come back to eat with you, okay?

122
00:11:12,039 --> 00:11:12,759
There's a bed upstairs.

123
00:11:17,320 --> 00:11:19,080
You're gonna crash and fix

124
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:19,759
your jet lag now?

125
00:11:22,559 --> 00:11:23,120
Let's go.

126
00:11:24,679 --> 00:11:25,200
Mr. Liu,

127
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:26,240
I left your keys in the car.

128
00:11:26,360 --> 00:11:27,080
I'll head up then.
Alright. Thanks.

129
00:11:31,799 --> 00:11:33,080
Then I'll drop Miss Ruan off first.

130
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:40,919
Than...

131
00:11:45,240 --> 00:11:46,120
Thank you, Mr. Liu.

132
00:11:50,120 --> 00:11:50,720
No problem, Ruan Yu.
You take the back.

133
00:11:51,519 --> 00:11:52,440
More comfortable back there.

134
00:11:55,559 --> 00:11:56,399
Thanks, Mr. Liu.

135
00:12:04,240 --> 00:12:05,000
Close the door yourself.

136
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:24,399
Mr. Liu, I'm not going home.

137
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:25,840
Can you drop me at a friend's place?

138
00:12:28,600 --> 00:12:29,200
Sure.

139
00:12:31,159 --> 00:12:31,919
It's not out of the way.

140
00:12:32,200 --> 00:12:33,080
It's actually closer.

141
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:34,600
No problem.

142
00:12:34,720 --> 00:12:36,000
Just send me the address.

143
00:12:36,519 --> 00:12:36,960
Okay.

144
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:12,039
Miss Ruan.

145
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:14,000
Mind telling me

146
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,200
which friend you're going to?

147
00:13:16,879 --> 00:13:18,159
That's a little direct, don't you think?

148
00:13:19,799 --> 00:13:20,360
You ask her then.

149
00:13:24,960 --> 00:13:25,759
My editor's place.

150
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:29,399
Got it.

151
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:32,879
Going to your editor's?

152
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:40,679
What's up?

153
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:42,399
The case didn't go through?

154
00:13:43,840 --> 00:13:44,320
Mingying.

155
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,279
Guess
who I ran into today?

156
00:13:47,879 --> 00:13:48,759
Liu Mao...

157
00:13:50,559 --> 00:13:51,399
He confessed to you?

158
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:53,519
It's Xu Huaisong.

159
00:13:54,519 --> 00:13:55,159
Mingying.

160
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:57,360
I met
the real Xu Huaisong.

161
00:14:04,919 --> 00:14:06,159
Something's off.

162
00:14:07,200 --> 00:14:09,559
It's perfectly normal for me to care

163
00:14:09,559 --> 00:14:11,200
about who I'm being set up with.

164
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:12,480
Then why

165
00:14:12,840 --> 00:14:15,000
are you so worried about it?

166
00:14:17,320 --> 00:14:19,159
Gotta know where my client's going.

167
00:14:20,279 --> 00:14:21,159
Problem?

168
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:23,759
She's already out there

169
00:14:23,759 --> 00:14:24,679
looking for a boyfriend.

170
00:14:25,440 --> 00:14:26,159
Where else would she go?

171
00:14:26,600 --> 00:14:28,480
Just some regular friend's place.

172
00:14:29,519 --> 00:14:30,240
Easy for you
to say now.

173
00:14:31,960 --> 00:14:33,039
What if she only went on the blind date

174
00:14:33,039 --> 00:14:34,600
to get her family off her back?

175
00:14:34,919 --> 00:14:36,039
You think you know my date

176
00:14:36,039 --> 00:14:37,080
better than I do?

177
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:42,960
That call at the office this morning

178
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:43,840
was you,
wasn't it?

179
00:14:45,399 --> 00:14:46,480
Setting me up to leave?

180
00:14:47,639 --> 00:14:49,639
You're a little slow on the uptake.

181
00:14:50,159 --> 00:14:51,320
How'd you even become a lawyer?

182
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,399
Your ex-girlfriend?

183
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:03,759
Well,

184
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:07,320
it's complicated.

185
00:15:07,840 --> 00:15:10,120
What's more complicated

186
00:15:10,120 --> 00:15:11,360
than an ex?

187
00:15:13,519 --> 00:15:15,279
Don't you think debt and credit

188
00:15:15,279 --> 00:15:15,960
are more complicated?

189
00:15:17,919 --> 00:15:18,919
She owes you money?

190
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:23,519
No.

191
00:15:23,960 --> 00:15:24,919
Then what's the deal between you two?
Just say it.

192
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:26,480
Spit it out.

193
00:15:26,480 --> 00:15:27,519
Chinese food or Western food?

194
00:15:28,159 --> 00:15:28,919
Fine, don't tell me.

195
00:15:30,840 --> 00:15:31,600
I'm good with anything.
I'm not hungry. Up to you.

196
00:15:33,960 --> 00:15:35,039
When are you leaving this time?

197
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:36,799
Tomorrow.

198
00:15:38,399 --> 00:15:39,320
You just got back yesterday
and you're leaving tomorrow?

199
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:42,200
My client's trial

200
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:43,840
is in less than 48 hours.

201
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:44,759
Think I should be in a hurry?

202
00:15:45,159 --> 00:15:45,759
Then why'd you

203
00:15:45,759 --> 00:15:47,120
even bother coming back now?

204
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:57,399
What is

205
00:15:57,399 --> 00:15:59,919
more important than a trial?

206
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:03,200
Excuse me.

207
00:16:05,639 --> 00:16:06,000
Hello?

208
00:16:06,679 --> 00:16:07,320
Huaisong.

209
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:09,720
I think I messed up.

210
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:12,639
I think I might've

211
00:16:12,639 --> 00:16:13,480
screwed Ruan Yu over.

212
00:16:19,039 --> 00:16:20,000
Who did you just say?

213
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:21,879
Ruan Yu.

214
00:16:21,879 --> 00:16:22,799
You forgot?

215
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:34,559
Take it easy.

216
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:36,120
Just take your time.

217
00:16:37,519 --> 00:16:38,960
I don't know what to do.

218
00:16:40,759 --> 00:16:42,080
I'll send you a photo.

219
00:16:47,759 --> 00:16:48,320
Huaisong!

220
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:50,039
Here's the document you needed.

221
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:54,960
That night,

222
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:57,320
I found this in the piano room

223
00:16:57,679 --> 00:16:58,600
at the school art gallery.

224
00:17:08,160 --> 00:17:09,920
You spend over ten hours flying back,

225
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:11,079
stay for a day,

226
00:17:11,440 --> 00:17:13,160
then fly another ten-plus hours back.

227
00:17:14,039 --> 00:17:15,160
I think you've lost it.

228
00:17:17,759 --> 00:17:19,000
Who wouldn't?

229
00:17:21,519 --> 00:17:22,079
Crazy.

230
00:17:23,319 --> 00:17:24,599
I'm losing it.

231
00:17:26,119 --> 00:17:28,079
Who was it that swore up and down

232
00:17:28,319 --> 00:17:29,720
they wouldn't get caught?

233
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:32,400
This is insane.

234
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:33,720
I never thought it'd actually

235
00:17:33,720 --> 00:17:35,039
make its way to him.

236
00:17:36,079 --> 00:17:37,519
You wouldn't even see this in a novel.

237
00:17:39,279 --> 00:17:40,200
What do I do?

238
00:17:41,039 --> 00:17:42,119
I put out a post saying

239
00:17:42,119 --> 00:17:43,640
the novel was based on my real life,

240
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,440
and also shared a video

241
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:46,400
clarifying the timeline
of the outline.

242
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:49,359
Can't delete or change it now.

243
00:17:50,519 --> 00:17:52,599
What if... What if

244
00:17:52,599 --> 00:17:53,160
he sees it?

245
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:56,920
Don't worry about that for now.

246
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,640
Isn't he some hotshot American lawyer?

247
00:17:59,759 --> 00:18:00,720
Probably doesn't have time
to scroll through your Weibo.

248
00:18:01,799 --> 00:18:02,599
Plus, you said
he didn't even recognize you.

249
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:05,039
But what if...

250
00:18:06,039 --> 00:18:06,960
What if he reads

251
00:18:06,960 --> 00:18:08,480
Chapter 23?

252
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:09,559
You were the one

253
00:18:09,559 --> 00:18:10,960
who added that wild scene.

254
00:18:11,359 --> 00:18:13,039
No, no, no... I...

255
00:18:13,039 --> 00:18:13,640
I'm gonna...

256
00:18:14,519 --> 00:18:15,680
I'm locking that chapter right now.

257
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:17,599
Locking it now.

258
00:18:19,519 --> 00:18:20,440
But seriously,

259
00:18:20,759 --> 00:18:21,680
you're dropping the lawsuit
over this little mess?

260
00:18:22,799 --> 00:18:23,359
No!

261
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:25,039
I'm definitely suing.

262
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:26,920
I don't believe

263
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:28,440
Hang City

264
00:18:28,599 --> 00:18:29,880
doesn't have a better law firm.

265
00:19:02,759 --> 00:19:03,599
You two know each other?

266
00:19:08,319 --> 00:19:09,599
No. No, we don't.

267
00:19:15,319 --> 00:19:15,839
No.

268
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,200
Good thing he doesn't remember me.

269
00:19:36,240 --> 00:19:36,839
[These law firms]
[were recommended by a friend.]

270
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:38,799
[I've already made appointments.]

271
00:19:38,920 --> 00:19:40,240
[You can just go tomorrow.]

272
00:19:42,799 --> 00:19:43,839
[As expected, you're the one]

273
00:19:43,839 --> 00:19:44,960
[I can count on]

274
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:45,480
[when it counts.]

275
00:19:52,079 --> 00:19:53,200
We know copyright disputes

276
00:19:53,200 --> 00:19:54,720
inside out. You'll win for sure!

277
00:19:55,400 --> 00:19:56,000
So

278
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,079
what's your level as a writer?

279
00:19:57,400 --> 00:19:58,400
How much do you make from a book?

280
00:20:00,519 --> 00:20:01,240
Ms. Ruan,

281
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,960
what Mr. Chen is saying

282
00:20:02,960 --> 00:20:04,200
is that these cases are better

283
00:20:04,200 --> 00:20:04,960
settled out of court.

284
00:20:05,319 --> 00:20:06,839
Mr. Chen means

285
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:08,960
a PR battle costs a lot.

286
00:20:09,640 --> 00:20:10,880
Mr. Chen...

287
00:20:11,039 --> 00:20:12,519
Follow me right now,

288
00:20:12,519 --> 00:20:13,480
and let's do some
public interactions.

289
00:20:14,839 --> 00:20:15,839
